{"id":73221,"title":"Cancer patients' perspectives on multidisciplinary team working: an exploratory focus group study.","abstract":"This qualitative, focus-group study explores what patients understand about the multidisciplinary team (MDT) in cancer care. Participants were positive towards MDT working, and by strengthening the role of nurses in MDT decision-making, the representation of patients' interests can be improved.","date":"2014-06-12","categories":"Neoplasms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24919246","annotations":[{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.219609,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Oncology","weight":0.130565,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oncology"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.0332387,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"Focus group","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Focus_group"},{"name":"Group representation","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_representation"},{"name":"Qualitative research","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qualitative_research"},{"name":"Multidisciplinarity","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multidisciplinarity"},{"name":"Social group","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_group"},{"name":"Mountain Time Zone","weight":0.013127,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mountain_Time_Zone"}]}
